# RunPod Assistant Data

Knowledge base data repository for the RunPod Assistant. Changes to `knowledge/` or `scraped/` directories on `main` automatically trigger a Mastra knowledge ingestion workflow.

## GitHub Actions Setup

The workflow at `.github/workflows/trigger-knowledge-ingestion.yml` requires the following configuration in your GitHub repository settings.

### 1. Repository Variable

Go to **Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions > Variables** and add:

| Name | Value |
|------|-------|
| `MASTRA_BASE_URL` | The base URL of your Mastra deployment (e.g. `https://runpod-assistant.mastra.cloud`) |

### 2. Repository Secret

Go to **Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions > Secrets** and add:

| Name | Value |
|------|-------|
| `RUNPOD_ASSISTANT_API_KEY` | API key for authenticating with the Mastra workflow API |

### 3. Triggering

The workflow runs automatically when files under `knowledge/` or `scraped/` are pushed to `main`. It can also be triggered manually from the **Actions** tab via `workflow_dispatch`.
